1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,680
We need lyrics that cut deep.

2
00:02:35,280 --> 00:02:38,040
So when Puna sings, people cry.

3
00:02:38,760 --> 00:02:41,160
Should we have
Teacher Mueangphrai write it?

4
00:02:41,760 --> 00:02:42,720
Teacher, can you do it?

5
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:43,960
Yes.

6
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:46,040
Once it's ready, I'll present it.

7
00:02:46,120 --> 00:02:47,600
My girlfriend, Aew,

8
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,760
says the shop was ordered
to move the goods.

9
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:51,160
The goods aren't in the shop.

10
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:53,720
Try following the guy named Tia.

11
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,520
Okay, understood.

12
00:02:55,600 --> 00:02:58,240
There's a mole in our group.

13
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,480
We need to find him.

14
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,680
The car's in bad shape.
It might need a garage.

15
00:03:03,760 --> 00:03:05,640
Follow them first.

16
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,240
We'll deal with the car later.

17
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,680
I want you to take out
Captain Tom, understand?

18
00:03:10,760 --> 00:03:11,720
Hey, grenade! Take cover!

19
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,480
PREVIOUS EPISODE

20
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,640
What do we do?

21
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:18,960
Captain Tom's at a disadvantage.

22
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,600
What the hell are you doing?!

23
00:03:33,480 --> 00:03:35,200
Whoa! Chit, don't shoot! Don't!

24
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,720
Damn it! Why are you getting in the way?

25
00:03:37,800 --> 00:03:38,720
Chit!

26
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,960
Move out of the way!

27
00:03:40,040 --> 00:03:41,920
The car's dead. It won't start.

28
00:03:46,720 --> 00:03:48,280
Who the hell? Fall back!

29
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:49,320
Go!

30
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,880
Chit! Help me!

31
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,960
Chit!

32
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:02,040
If Chaiya hadn't stepped in,

33
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:03,520
we'd be wiped out for sure.

34
00:04:04,120 --> 00:04:05,480
Don't say a word, Corporal Chom.
Stay quiet.

35
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,320
Central Investigation,
thanks for coming to help.

36
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:13,600
Are you okay, Captain?

37
00:04:14,200 --> 00:04:16,079
I'm fine, but my men are injured.

38
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:18,399
-Take care of them.
-Understood, sir.

39
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:25,040
Drop the gun.

40
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:29,640
Hands up.

41
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:32,520
Hands up!

42
00:04:35,200 --> 00:04:36,560
Surrender, Tia.

43
00:04:37,280 --> 00:04:38,840
There's no way you're escaping now.

44
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:54,160
DARATHONG MUSIC

45
00:04:55,880 --> 00:04:56,760
Come in.

46
00:05:00,680 --> 00:05:02,360
Yes, Mr. Singha.

47
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:06,480
You helped Captain Tom, didn't you?

48
00:05:09,120 --> 00:05:11,240
No, I didn't help.

49
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:13,240
You guys stepped in.

50
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:15,720
You blocked the bullets for him.

51
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,960
It wasn't like that.

52
00:05:18,040 --> 00:05:20,240
The van was out of control.
The brakes were shot.

53
00:05:20,320 --> 00:05:21,280
You're lying!

54
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:23,280
Chit, you saw it.

55
00:05:23,360 --> 00:05:25,160
I was fixing the car
in front of the company.

56
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,400
It was an accident.

57
00:05:30,480 --> 00:05:32,240
We didn't mean for it to happen.

58
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:47,680
Are you sure you're not lying?

59
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:55,600
Yes, I'm telling the truth.

60
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:12,560
You're a police informant, aren't you?

61
00:06:26,040 --> 00:06:27,480
Boss, it's Chart.

62
00:06:29,080 --> 00:06:30,440
Put it on speaker.

63
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:33,240
<i>Boss.</i>

64
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:36,200
We found the one who's a police informant.

65
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,320
Who?

66
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:41,080
Aew, Tia's subordinate.

67
00:06:41,160 --> 00:06:43,360
Her boyfriend is Weerachai.

68
00:06:45,640 --> 00:06:46,840
Thanks.

69
00:06:53,560 --> 00:06:55,000
I swear,

70
00:06:55,520 --> 00:06:57,200
I'm not a police informant.

71
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,320
Same here.

72
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:02,960
The car was already broken.

73
00:07:03,040 --> 00:07:04,440
You know that, Mr. Kitti.

74
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,320
He said that before we left.

75
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,000
Maybe…

76
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:18,840
it's the truth.

77
00:07:32,120 --> 00:07:33,520
Tell me!

78
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:35,040
Where did he run off to?

79
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:36,600
Tell me!

80
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,680
I really don't know.

81
00:07:38,760 --> 00:07:41,320
Honestly, I don't know!

82
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:43,240
Not telling, huh?

83
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,520
This time, I'll let you two go.

84
00:08:03,840 --> 00:08:06,560
But I'll be watching you closely.

85
00:08:06,640 --> 00:08:08,320
The moment you betray me,

86
00:08:09,480 --> 00:08:11,080
you're dead.

87
00:08:43,720 --> 00:08:45,480
<i>Now, my dream</i>

88
00:08:45,560 --> 00:08:47,440
<i>is finally coming true.</i>

89
00:08:48,720 --> 00:08:52,400
<i>Please let everything go smoothly.</i>

90
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:56,600
<i>I hope I get a great song to sing.</i>

91
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,200
<i>I promise</i>

92
00:09:00,080 --> 00:09:02,960
<i>I'll sing my heart out.</i>

93
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,000
<i>I'll give it my all,</i>

94
00:09:07,920 --> 00:09:10,680
<i>to honor the kindness of those</i>
<i>who gave me this chance</i>

95
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:34,200
No one's luckier than me.

96
00:09:34,280 --> 00:09:37,680
Not only has the label
kindly given me the chance to sing,

97
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,920
but they also support me

98
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:41,640
in doing outside activities.

99
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,200
Today, I'm doing a good deed

100
00:09:43,280 --> 00:09:44,880
by sweeping the temple grounds.

101
00:09:44,960 --> 00:09:47,840
Honestly, being a singer

102
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,520
isn't just about having a good voice.

103
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,920
Your heart and mind

104
00:09:51,000 --> 00:09:53,520
also need to be pure.

105
00:09:54,560 --> 00:09:56,320
Start with small good deeds,

106
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,360
like the one I'm doing today. Oops!

107
00:09:58,880 --> 00:10:00,200
Everyone!

108
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:02,720
I need to end the livestream now.

109
00:10:02,800 --> 00:10:05,920
I have to finish cleaning.

110
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:09,200
-See you later. Bye!
-Cut!

111
00:10:10,320 --> 00:10:11,840
Great job, Miss Maria!

112
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:13,760
You look amazing!

113
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,560
Enough. I'm lazy. It's way too hot.

114
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,520
Miss Maria.

115
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:20,680
You've only swept twice!

116
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,680
Sweep more, so it looks believable.

117
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:26,160
Why sweep more? It's just for show.
We don't have to actually clean.

118
00:10:26,240 --> 00:10:28,720
If you're doing good deeds,
you have to sweep properly!

119
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:30,480
Two quick sweeps won't do.

120
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:31,840
If you really want to sweep

121
00:10:31,920 --> 00:10:33,320
and do a good deed, go ahead!

122
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,440
Let's go, Miss Maria.

123
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,240
Fine!

124
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:41,440
I'll show you!

125
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,000
I'll sweep the whole temple!

126
00:10:43,520 --> 00:10:46,880
What's there to be scared of?
Someone like me…

127
00:10:46,960 --> 00:10:48,000
Hey!

128
00:10:48,520 --> 00:10:50,200
This has nothing to do with me.

129
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:52,120
Wait!

130
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:53,480
Better go this way.

131
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:54,920
Maria!

132
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:56,040
Maria!

133
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,360
Yes, Boss.

134
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:59,760
I've arrived at Khok Ta Yu village.

135
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,440
My first task

136
00:11:01,520 --> 00:11:03,680
is to interview a new singer named Maria

137
00:11:03,760 --> 00:11:05,400
from Darathong Music.

138
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,640
Oh my, Miss Maria, you're so cute!

139
00:11:08,720 --> 00:11:10,040
Hello, Miss Maria.

140
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,560
May I interview you for a bit?

141
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,480
Excuse me.

142
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:15,640
What would you be interviewing her for?

143
00:11:15,720 --> 00:11:18,640
I run a channel, you know.
I'm hoping for lots of likes.

144
00:11:18,720 --> 00:11:21,480
The views will probably go
through the roof.

145
00:11:21,560 --> 00:11:23,440
Well, is there a cut in it for us, Auntie?

146
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:27,520
There's a cut too?

147
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:31,000
People should know
how to show appreciation.

148
00:11:31,080 --> 00:11:33,280
If you're making money,
you should share it.

149
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,520
Okay?

150
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,800
If not, then I'm afraid
we can't do the interview.

151
00:11:36,880 --> 00:11:38,520
-Okay, Auntie?
-Alright.

152
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,640
Never mind then. I won't do the interview.

153
00:11:40,720 --> 00:11:42,440
If you're not going to interview,
then leave.

154
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:43,800
Bye.

155
00:11:43,880 --> 00:11:44,880
What's with her?

156
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,480
Sophie, is it really okay to do this?

157
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:51,640
All the famous singers
and celebrities do it like this.

158
00:11:51,720 --> 00:11:55,400
Miss Maria, they don't just let people
take advantage of them.

159
00:11:57,880 --> 00:12:00,200
Maria, can we take a photo with you?

160
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,240
Sure.

161
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,640
That's enough for now.

162
00:12:11,720 --> 00:12:13,160
Miss Maria isn't available right now.

163
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,280
Sophie!

164
00:12:14,360 --> 00:12:15,960
Miss Maria, look over there.

165
00:12:18,200 --> 00:12:19,640
Excuse us.

166
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:24,360
Sorry about that. She's really busy today.
We'll do it another time.

167
00:12:30,360 --> 00:12:31,960
What do you three want?

168
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,240
Nothing really.

169
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:37,880
Just here to say hi to an old friend
from our company.

170
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:42,360
How's your new company treating you?

171
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,840
Have they let you sing yet?

172
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:49,640
Are you still just ironing clothes
like before?

173
00:12:51,120 --> 00:12:52,160
Maybe she's cleaning toilets

174
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,840
or scrubbing them. Who knows.

175
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,560
I told you already.

176
00:13:03,400 --> 00:13:05,640
Just focus on your own jobs.

177
00:13:06,320 --> 00:13:08,120
Don't meddle in others' business.

178
00:13:09,600 --> 00:13:13,040
Whether I get to sing or not,

179
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:15,200
you'll find out soon enough.

180
00:13:16,800 --> 00:13:19,160
Excuse me. I've got things to do.

181
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,600
Acting all that tough.

182
00:13:27,360 --> 00:13:29,600
She just called us nosy.

183
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:31,480
-In other words…
-I know!

184
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:33,640
No need to rub it in.

185
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:37,320
Got it. I'll handle it.

186
00:13:44,800 --> 00:13:45,960
There you are.

187
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:48,200
Fate really brought us together.

188
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,360
What kind of songs
is Puna going to release?

189
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,760
That's got nothing to do with us.

190
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,640
You idiot, of course it does.

191
00:13:58,720 --> 00:14:00,760
If she releases songs
in the same style as Miss Maria,

192
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:03,280
she becomes her competitor.

193
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:04,520
Oh, right.

194
00:14:05,120 --> 00:14:06,120
Maria.

195
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:11,240
That's the host who got us scolded.

196
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:13,560
You're right. So annoying.

197
00:14:15,040 --> 00:14:17,680
Sorry, are you a fan of Maria?

198
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:21,040
I'm afraid we'll have to leave now.
Maria is fully booked today.

199
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:23,360
Don't you remember me?

200
00:14:23,440 --> 00:14:25,160
I'm Praewa, the host

201
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:28,400
who interviewed you on the show. Remember?

202
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:31,640
I remember. Hello again.

203
00:14:32,240 --> 00:14:33,640
Oh, it's you!

204
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:35,400
The show host.

205
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:42,240
I was hoping to get
a quick interview with you today.

206
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:43,720
Sure.

207
00:14:44,480 --> 00:14:45,800
Hey, wait a second.

208
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:49,880
Miss Maria already has a livestream
scheduled at the company today.

209
00:14:53,680 --> 00:14:56,680
Then can I follow and film it?

210
00:14:56,760 --> 00:14:59,520
We can do the interview
after the livestream.

211
00:15:00,560 --> 00:15:01,400
We're really sorry,

212
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:03,320
but actually,

213
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:06,000
if you didn't book in advance,
we really can't give you a slot.

214
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,760
Exactly.

215
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,560
We must stick to the schedule.

216
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:12,160
Coming unannounced like this

217
00:15:12,240 --> 00:15:13,440
doesn't give her time to prepare.

218
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:15,960
We'll have to go now.

219
00:15:16,040 --> 00:15:17,480
Let's go, Miss Maria.

220
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:19,360
-See you later.
-Okay.

221
00:15:20,040 --> 00:15:21,480
Sorry about that.

222
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:30,200
Why are they so hard to get today?

223
00:15:34,120 --> 00:15:35,320
Boss.

224
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,160
I've found Maria,

225
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:38,840
but her manager said no interview

226
00:15:38,920 --> 00:15:40,480
because we didn't book in advance.

227
00:15:43,560 --> 00:15:46,520
I also didn't expect her
to be this hard to reach.

228
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,080
Huh?

229
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:51,160
Find someone else?

230
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:54,840
Yes, I'll try to look for someone else.

231
00:15:58,800 --> 00:15:59,880
Hey!

232
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,600
What are you secretly filming?

233
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:09,280
No, I'm not filming you.

234
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,800
Wow.

235
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:15,000
You've got an expensive phone too.

236
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:17,120
Hey, give me your phone.

237
00:16:18,160 --> 00:16:19,720
-Don't come any closer.
-Give it here!

238
00:16:21,440 --> 00:16:23,360
Help!

239
00:16:23,440 --> 00:16:25,120
Where do you think you're going?

240
00:16:25,840 --> 00:16:27,000
Give it here.

241
00:16:28,280 --> 00:16:29,200
Who the hell?

242
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:40,240
Hit me again. I like it!

243
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:42,920
One more time!

244
00:16:48,840 --> 00:16:50,800
Let's go! Run!

245
00:16:51,720 --> 00:16:53,080
Get up!

246
00:16:53,160 --> 00:16:54,240
After them!

247
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:56,480
They're catching up!

248
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,040
Oh, I tripped!

249
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:01,040
Hey, watch out!

250
00:17:07,160 --> 00:17:08,640
Hey, picking on women?

251
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,000
Are they filming a movie?

252
00:17:15,079 --> 00:17:16,880
Oh my, I should get closer.

253
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,440
If they see how pretty I am,
they'll cast me as the heroine.

254
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,960
It's not a movie shoot. Don't go there!

255
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:24,520
Can't you see there's a fight going on?

256
00:17:24,599 --> 00:17:25,640
They're really fighting?

257
00:17:28,119 --> 00:17:29,640
Chaiya!

258
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,720
-Don't kick me again!
-Why not?

259
00:17:38,800 --> 00:17:40,600
-I don't like it!
-Too late.

260
00:17:44,120 --> 00:17:45,440
-Hey! Is that a knife?
-Stop!

261
00:17:45,520 --> 00:17:46,760
I said stop!

262
00:17:48,600 --> 00:17:49,440
Oh no!

263
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:50,680
-Police!
-Hey, run!

264
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:51,920
The cops are here.

265
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,600
Stop right there!

266
00:18:01,480 --> 00:18:03,840
Don't you dare arrest these two.
Absolutely not!

267
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:04,840
Why is that?

268
00:18:04,920 --> 00:18:05,960
Why?

269
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:07,520
Because they're not criminals.

270
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,080
So don't you come any closer!

271
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,960
But I need to talk to them.

272
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:12,440
Don't you dare come any closer!

273
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:14,680
If you don't believe me,
I'll record it and expose you.

274
00:18:14,760 --> 00:18:16,440
This phone can record video

275
00:18:16,520 --> 00:18:17,760
and send it on texts.

276
00:18:17,840 --> 00:18:20,400
It can go straight to major news outlets.

277
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:21,560
Want that? Look at them.

278
00:18:21,640 --> 00:18:24,000
Look at these poor innocent citizens!

279
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:26,200
These two are not criminals.

280
00:18:26,280 --> 00:18:27,840
They're the ones who actually helped us.

281
00:18:29,840 --> 00:18:31,080
Did you hear that?

282
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:32,760
The victim came to speak for them,

283
00:18:32,840 --> 00:18:34,840
confirming they're not criminals.

284
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,040
WEERAPHON PAKDEEKIT

285
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:44,080
Hey, it's you.

286
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:46,400
You are…

287
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:49,400
Praewa! The pigtail girl from the back row

288
00:18:49,480 --> 00:18:51,200
who used to stick her nose
in everything, right?

289
00:18:51,280 --> 00:18:54,360
Yeah. But now I'm a reporter.

290
00:18:54,880 --> 00:18:56,880
If you do anything wrong,

291
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,760
I won't go easy on you.

292
00:19:01,440 --> 00:19:02,640
You two know each other?

293
00:19:03,720 --> 00:19:05,160
Don't call it that.

294
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:08,480
We're bad karma for each other.

295
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:15,840
I have plenty of witnesses

296
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:16,840
proving I'm not the criminal.

297
00:19:17,440 --> 00:19:19,840
This time, you can't arrest me.

298
00:19:20,760 --> 00:19:22,080
Don't mess with the public.

299
00:19:22,160 --> 00:19:23,600
Everyone has phones now.

300
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:25,640
If the police do anything wrong,

301
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:27,480
you'll get exposed.

302
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,480
That's right.

303
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:31,720
If anyone bullies them,

304
00:19:31,800 --> 00:19:33,640
I'll protect them myself.

305
00:19:35,080 --> 00:19:36,040
Alright.

306
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:37,880
I won't arrest you.

307
00:19:38,560 --> 00:19:41,040
But if I catch you
doing anything wrong again,

308
00:19:41,120 --> 00:19:42,840
I won't let you off next time.

309
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:47,480
Oh my, I can't handle the sight of blood.
I'm going to faint!

310
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:53,160
Please come with us to give statements.

311
00:19:53,240 --> 00:19:55,200
I'll make sure these two thugs go to jail.

312
00:19:55,800 --> 00:19:56,760
Sure!

313
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:00,440
-Let's go, Sergeant.
-Go!

314
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:02,400
Please leave.

315
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,400
The police are gone.

316
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:09,880
Are you guys okay?

317
00:20:10,800 --> 00:20:12,320
Yes, I'm fine.

318
00:20:12,840 --> 00:20:15,360
I was so nervous. Oh my.

319
00:20:15,440 --> 00:20:17,120
Your heart's still beating normally.

320
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:18,600
Okay, that's a relief then.

321
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:21,200
All good? You're okay, right?

322
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,120
I'm okay.

323
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:24,440
You alright?

324
00:20:25,640 --> 00:20:27,400
Just a bit bruised. I'm fine.

325
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:29,560
Okay. A woman's
got to take care of herself.

326
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:30,800
Good.

327
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:32,640
My name is Paula, okay?

328
00:20:32,720 --> 00:20:33,840
Remember that.

329
00:20:34,440 --> 00:20:36,200
-Paula.
-Somporn!

330
00:20:37,160 --> 00:20:38,440
Worst timing ever.

331
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:41,120
Why use my full name?

332
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,800
I told you to call me Madam Paula.

333
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:45,840
Anyway, when are you picking up
the fried fish cakes you ordered?

334
00:20:48,520 --> 00:20:50,360
What's with the fried fish cakes now?

335
00:20:50,440 --> 00:20:52,320
Can't you see
there are men in front of me?

336
00:20:52,400 --> 00:20:53,760
Let's talk over there.

337
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:54,760
I won't run off.

338
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:56,480
I'll definitely pay
for the fried fish cakes.

339
00:21:00,480 --> 00:21:01,560
I remember now.

340
00:21:02,160 --> 00:21:03,600
You're the host from the music show

341
00:21:03,680 --> 00:21:05,760
Maria was interviewed on, right?
I was there too.

342
00:21:06,640 --> 00:21:07,840
I was part of the crew.

343
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,960
That's right.

344
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:14,560
Sorry, there were so many people that day,
I didn't really notice.

345
00:21:18,280 --> 00:21:19,240
I'm late.

346
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:21,400
I need to go shoot some stock footage.

347
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:23,600
Do you know
any nice scenic spots around here?

348
00:21:23,680 --> 00:21:24,720
Oh.

349
00:21:25,280 --> 00:21:26,440
There are tons of spots

350
00:21:26,520 --> 00:21:28,760
around here. I'll take you there.

351
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:31,800
Then I'll head off first.

352
00:21:31,880 --> 00:21:33,040
-See you.
-Okay.

353
00:21:33,120 --> 00:21:35,160
-This way, please.
-Thank you.

354
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:47,240
Thanks for helping me back there.

355
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:50,600
This is what you call…

356
00:21:51,280 --> 00:21:52,800
destiny.

357
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,400
Ugh!

358
00:21:54,480 --> 00:21:57,120
Do you think
you're some K-drama hero or what?

359
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:59,840
If I'm the hero of a K-drama,

360
00:21:59,920 --> 00:22:01,880
then you must be…

361
00:22:03,720 --> 00:22:05,520
I am not your heroine.

362
00:22:08,600 --> 00:22:10,880
But if you were my heroine,

363
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:14,600
then I'd have a scene
where I'd go after you,

364
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:17,080
I'd pin you down.

365
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:20,440
What are you talking about, you pervert?

366
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,120
-You crazy!
-That hurts!

367
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,520
Acting like it hurts?

368
00:22:23,600 --> 00:22:24,440
You didn't even hit me.

369
00:22:37,960 --> 00:22:39,000
I miss you.

370
00:22:56,480 --> 00:22:58,240
How's your new company?

371
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:00,440
Have you got a song to sing yet?

372
00:23:03,680 --> 00:23:05,600
We're still looking for songs.

373
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:07,880
Today I came to the temple to pray

374
00:23:07,960 --> 00:23:08,920
and ask for blessings.

375
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,080
I'm rooting for you, Puna.

376
00:23:13,960 --> 00:23:16,040
I hope you become the singer
you've always dreamed of.

377
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:20,920
You should take care of yourself too.

378
00:23:21,640 --> 00:23:24,040
Don't do anything too risky.

379
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:26,480
May you be protected.

380
00:23:41,320 --> 00:23:43,120
May everything you just said

381
00:23:44,800 --> 00:23:46,400
come back to you as well.

382
00:23:48,800 --> 00:23:50,800
I'm glad you're worried about me.

383
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,640
You dropped this locket.

384
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:21,480
Where did you find it?

385
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:23,440
I thought it was gone.

386
00:24:24,840 --> 00:24:26,640
Thank you, Chaiya!

387
00:24:26,720 --> 00:24:28,040
Thank you!

388
00:24:28,560 --> 00:24:29,640
Yay!

389
00:24:45,920 --> 00:24:47,040
I should go.

390
00:24:47,120 --> 00:24:48,120
I've got something to do.

391
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,240
See you.

392
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:31,400
Thank you, Chaiya!

393
00:25:31,480 --> 00:25:32,800
Thank you!

394
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:34,800
Yay!

395
00:25:40,960 --> 00:25:44,880
DARATHONG MUSIC

396
00:25:44,960 --> 00:25:46,120
How's it going?

397
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:48,640
You've had your men
watching Tharin for days.

398
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:49,560
Any progress?

399
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:53,600
Nothing unusual so far.

400
00:25:53,680 --> 00:25:54,800
But…

401
00:25:54,880 --> 00:25:55,960
But what?

402
00:25:58,080 --> 00:25:59,560
I'm starting to suspect

403
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,960
the person we think is Tharin

404
00:26:03,040 --> 00:26:04,480
might actually be Phupha.

405
00:26:06,680 --> 00:26:08,760
How is that even possible?

406
00:26:09,680 --> 00:26:12,160
Didn't you already kill him?

407
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,360
Yes.

408
00:26:14,280 --> 00:26:17,720
But you said Tharin
doesn't know how to fight.

409
00:26:17,800 --> 00:26:19,400
From what I saw,

410
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:20,760
that level of skill

411
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:22,840
definitely wasn't a coincidence.

412
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:25,640
What do we do, Singha?

413
00:26:25,720 --> 00:26:26,960
Should we just capture him?

414
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:28,920
Not yet.

415
00:26:30,080 --> 00:26:31,320
That would make things messy.

416
00:26:34,520 --> 00:26:35,920
There's something else.

417
00:26:36,840 --> 00:26:39,480
I'm suspicious about the woman
who was wearing a headscarf

418
00:26:39,560 --> 00:26:40,920
next to Tharin.

419
00:26:42,440 --> 00:26:43,400
His wife?

420
00:26:43,480 --> 00:26:45,320
I don't think so.

421
00:26:46,600 --> 00:26:48,960
I think that woman might be…

422
00:26:55,160 --> 00:26:56,760
Onanong?

423
00:26:59,920 --> 00:27:01,240
That's impossible.

424
00:27:02,160 --> 00:27:04,280
You killed them yourself.

425
00:27:05,040 --> 00:27:07,480
The car even exploded
right in front of you, didn't it?

426
00:27:10,360 --> 00:27:11,520
Wait.

427
00:27:12,080 --> 00:27:13,040
Let's do it like this.

428
00:27:14,720 --> 00:27:15,960
Send your men to keep watch

429
00:27:16,040 --> 00:27:17,920
on both Tharin
and the woman in the headscarf.

430
00:27:19,480 --> 00:27:20,640
Find out exactly

431
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:22,080
who they are.

432
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:24,520
Yes.

433
00:27:27,240 --> 00:27:31,400
Also, when I was investigating
Weerachai and Aew,

434
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:32,920
some villagers around there

435
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:35,600
said Weerachai was talking to two men

436
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,080
right before the incident.

437
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,440
Two men?

438
00:27:40,840 --> 00:27:43,920
You mean Chaiya and Manat, right?

439
00:27:44,640 --> 00:27:45,640
Yes, I think so.

440
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:49,160
Enough guessing.

441
00:27:50,880 --> 00:27:52,320
Can we just search their house?

442
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,200
Good. Good idea.

443
00:27:57,360 --> 00:27:58,920
Go get ready.

444
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:02,280
Prepare your men. I'll clear the way.

445
00:28:02,360 --> 00:28:03,560
Got it, sir.

446
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,200
Hello.

447
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,080
Chaiya.

448
00:28:14,360 --> 00:28:16,400
I've got an urgent job for you today.

449
00:28:17,320 --> 00:28:18,840
Bring Manat with you.

450
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:23,000
Come to the office now. Right away.

451
00:28:24,800 --> 00:28:26,640
Good. See you soon.

452
00:28:43,600 --> 00:28:45,480
You called us. Is there something urgent?

453
00:28:45,560 --> 00:28:48,640
Kitti and I are going to visit
a friend outside the city,

454
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,920
so we want you two to come with us.

455
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,960
Mr. Singha's worried
about potential ambushes,

456
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:58,040
so he wants capable people
along for protection.

457
00:28:59,080 --> 00:29:00,240
Of course.

458
00:29:01,800 --> 00:29:03,360
Let's go then. We're running late.

459
00:29:10,960 --> 00:29:12,080
You guys don't need to come.

460
00:29:12,680 --> 00:29:15,000
If you have any work,

461
00:29:15,080 --> 00:29:16,440
go finish it.

462
00:29:16,520 --> 00:29:18,120
Yes, Boss.

463
00:30:11,360 --> 00:30:12,520
We're getting off here?

464
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:16,280
But there aren't any houses around here.

465
00:30:17,360 --> 00:30:19,840
Walk a bit further in.
The house is inside.

466
00:30:19,920 --> 00:30:20,800
Let's go.

467
00:30:36,920 --> 00:30:38,320
Hey. Here it is.

468
00:30:38,400 --> 00:30:39,840
This is their place.

469
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:43,520
Got it. I'll be right back.

470
00:30:43,600 --> 00:30:44,720
Go, hurry up.

471
00:30:54,120 --> 00:30:55,960
Hope no one's home.

472
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:58,880
Aren't there just the two of them?

473
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:01,600
Let's go. The coast is clear.

474
00:31:02,120 --> 00:31:03,040
Hurry up.

475
00:31:16,280 --> 00:31:17,240
Hey.

476
00:31:17,320 --> 00:31:18,640
Let's split up and search.

477
00:31:19,160 --> 00:31:20,200
If you find anything, take photos.

478
00:31:21,120 --> 00:31:22,040
Yeah.

479
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:34,360
-I was gonna go to Ubon, Sakon Nakhon,
-There's someone here.

480
00:31:34,440 --> 00:31:36,080
and stop to rest in Yala,

481
00:31:36,160 --> 00:31:39,320
-and I'll come back here in the evening…
-I thought it was just the two of them.

482
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:41,040
He's in the shower.

483
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,920
-Keep searching. Quickly!
-Okay.

484
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:52,880
Check outside.

485
00:31:52,960 --> 00:31:54,000
You go outside!

486
00:32:01,680 --> 00:32:02,720
Let me carry it.

487
00:32:12,200 --> 00:32:13,640
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

488
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:18,680
Where are they going?

489
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:21,600
Around here,

490
00:32:21,680 --> 00:32:22,960
there shouldn't be any houses.

491
00:32:30,400 --> 00:32:31,280
Hey!

492
00:32:31,360 --> 00:32:32,640
He's done.

493
00:32:33,320 --> 00:32:34,360
Hide!

494
00:32:41,520 --> 00:32:44,440
<i>La, la, la, la</i>

495
00:32:44,520 --> 00:32:45,520
Whoo!

496
00:32:45,600 --> 00:32:46,880
How do I look, Sergeant Yot?

497
00:32:46,960 --> 00:32:48,640
I'm fresh out of the shower.
Handsome, right?

498
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:50,560
Who's more handsome, you or me?

499
00:32:50,640 --> 00:32:52,320
Obviously me! No need to answer.

500
00:32:55,840 --> 00:32:58,000
Why is it so hot in here?

501
00:32:58,080 --> 00:32:59,360
Is the AC broken or something?

502
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:02,280
My mouth's dry. I'm thirsty.

503
00:33:03,160 --> 00:33:06,200
I'm thirsty. I need some water.

504
00:33:08,920 --> 00:33:09,760
Here it is.

505
00:33:11,280 --> 00:33:12,880
At least there's one bottle left.

506
00:33:14,200 --> 00:33:15,440
What? Be quiet.

507
00:33:18,760 --> 00:33:20,280
This isn't mineral water!

508
00:33:21,120 --> 00:33:23,040
How many times do I have to say it?

509
00:33:24,480 --> 00:33:26,080
Sergeant Au only drinks mineral water

510
00:33:26,160 --> 00:33:28,000
from Mount Everest!

511
00:33:28,080 --> 00:33:30,800
That's how it should be!
This isn't right! Unacceptable!

512
00:33:32,520 --> 00:33:35,040
Hello? One, two, three.

513
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:36,240
I'd rather drink tap water.

514
00:33:38,080 --> 00:33:39,960
Hey, he's gone.

515
00:33:40,040 --> 00:33:41,560
-Yeah.
-Let's go.

516
00:33:46,800 --> 00:33:48,080
He's gone.

517
00:33:52,720 --> 00:33:53,560
Anything suspicious?

518
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:58,960
Nothing. But there's one room

519
00:33:59,040 --> 00:34:00,320
that looks really suspicious.

520
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:01,440
Which room?

521
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:03,600
Follow me.

522
00:34:13,560 --> 00:34:15,120
Where exactly are we going?

523
00:34:15,800 --> 00:34:17,679
There shouldn't be any houses around here.

524
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,679
Yeah.

525
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:21,239
The deeper we go,
the more isolated it gets. Are we lost?

526
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:29,040
We're here.

527
00:34:35,040 --> 00:34:36,320
Give me the basket.

528
00:34:47,360 --> 00:34:48,639
Hey!

529
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,040
What's going on here?

530
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:53,520
Hands up.

531
00:34:56,760 --> 00:34:58,000
Hands up!

532
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,320
What did we do wrong?

533
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,200
Yeah, exactly.

534
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:18,240
You two

535
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:20,880
are police informants, aren't you?

536
00:35:28,880 --> 00:35:29,880
Why are you asking that?

537
00:35:30,480 --> 00:35:32,800
Answer me!

538
00:35:32,880 --> 00:35:33,920
No.

539
00:35:34,440 --> 00:35:36,160
We're not police informants.

540
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,880
Why do you think we're informants?

541
00:35:39,960 --> 00:35:41,240
Don't act innocent.

542
00:35:44,760 --> 00:35:46,680
I know everything about you two.

543
00:35:49,440 --> 00:35:50,920
The two of us

544
00:35:51,520 --> 00:35:53,080
really don't have anything to hide.

545
00:35:53,680 --> 00:35:54,960
Don't trust them, Boss.

546
00:35:55,040 --> 00:35:57,240
I've been suspicious of them
from the start.

547
00:36:03,720 --> 00:36:07,080
I'll give you two a chance to run.

548
00:36:09,280 --> 00:36:11,400
But run well, run for your lives.

549
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:14,760
Because if you don't make it,

550
00:36:19,080 --> 00:36:20,440
you're dead.

551
00:36:22,040 --> 00:36:23,160
Got it?

552
00:36:40,120 --> 00:36:41,560
Hello.

553
00:36:41,640 --> 00:36:43,440
Anyone home?

554
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,800
Chaiya.

555
00:36:47,880 --> 00:36:50,480
I brought the clothes I ironed for you.

556
00:36:55,440 --> 00:36:56,640
This is the room.

557
00:36:58,240 --> 00:37:00,600
The most suspicious one. I'm telling you,

558
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:02,720
there must be
something important in there.

559
00:37:03,480 --> 00:37:04,800
Then open the door.

560
00:37:06,680 --> 00:37:07,520
Go on.

561
00:37:08,120 --> 00:37:10,160
Hey, just so you know,

562
00:37:10,240 --> 00:37:12,040
I'm not collecting the ironing fee today.

563
00:37:12,120 --> 00:37:14,600
I'm just here to deliver it,
so no need to hide.

564
00:37:19,680 --> 00:37:20,600
Hurry up!

565
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:24,880
Is no one home?

566
00:37:26,120 --> 00:37:27,960
I just heard someone inside.

567
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:29,920
Maybe I'm imagining it?

568
00:37:32,680 --> 00:37:33,560
Wait!

569
00:37:35,080 --> 00:37:37,480
No way! Chaiya!

570
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:39,760
Did he secretly bring a woman
into his room?

571
00:37:39,840 --> 00:37:42,360
That must be it. That's why
he won't open the door. Chaiya!

572
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:43,720
Chaiya!

573
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:47,560
That woman must be so shameless,

574
00:37:47,640 --> 00:37:49,320
staying in a man's room like this.

575
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,800
I have to see who she is!

576
00:37:50,880 --> 00:37:52,120
You shameless woman!

577
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:53,320
What should we do?

578
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:54,280
-If we stay here,
-Where?

579
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:55,920
-we're definitely getting caught.
-Where's that woman? Out!

580
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:57,080
Let's run! Go!

581
00:37:57,720 --> 00:37:59,720
I'm going to find out who you are.
You're shameless!

582
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:02,600
Chaiya! Huh?

583
00:38:04,720 --> 00:38:05,680
Where is he?

584
00:38:07,600 --> 00:38:08,920
Maybe no one's here.

585
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,280
Why is the doorknob like this?

586
00:38:18,200 --> 00:38:19,360
Oh no.

587
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:21,080
Who did…

588
00:38:28,440 --> 00:38:29,320
What was that?

589
00:38:31,720 --> 00:38:33,120
Am I hearing things?

590
00:38:34,200 --> 00:38:36,520
I just saw something.
Am I really hearing things?

591
00:38:37,600 --> 00:38:39,840
Am I getting old? No way!

592
00:38:39,920 --> 00:38:41,760
I'm still young.

593
00:38:41,840 --> 00:38:42,960
How could I be old?

594
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:46,680
Sergeant.

595
00:38:47,440 --> 00:38:49,720
You're always in this room.

596
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,000
Did you see anyone

597
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:53,800
coming in or going out
when Manat and Chaiya weren't here?

598
00:38:54,680 --> 00:38:55,520
Answer me.

599
00:38:57,400 --> 00:38:59,920
Weren't you always saying
you loved me so much?

600
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:02,680
Sergeant, say something!

601
00:39:04,560 --> 00:39:06,960
You're going to pretend to be silent, huh?

602
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:09,680
I won't even offer you food tomorrow,
just wait and see.

603
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:22,480
Is it…

604
00:39:22,560 --> 00:39:24,760
a ghost?

605
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,200
A ghost?

606
00:39:26,280 --> 00:39:27,320
Is this what they call…

607
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:29,160
a…

608
00:39:29,760 --> 00:39:31,320
a…

609
00:39:31,400 --> 00:39:33,440
a ghost?!

610
00:39:33,960 --> 00:39:36,200
It's a ghost!

611
00:39:38,800 --> 00:39:39,640
Please believe me.

612
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:42,880
We are not police informants.

613
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:46,320
You can check our background,
our phone records,

614
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:47,360
or anything.

615
00:39:50,560 --> 00:39:52,960
So they're choosing the hard way.

616
00:39:54,560 --> 00:39:56,800
Yeah. Do it.

617
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:00,000
Hey!

618
00:40:00,080 --> 00:40:01,160
-Hey!
-Let go.

619
00:40:03,400 --> 00:40:04,320
Fine.

620
00:40:05,520 --> 00:40:07,120
I'll give you a chance.

621
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:09,160
Manat.

622
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:11,440
Confess.

623
00:40:11,520 --> 00:40:12,720
Tell me who you are.

624
00:40:13,800 --> 00:40:15,560
If you confess,

625
00:40:16,160 --> 00:40:18,240
I might let you guys live.

626
00:40:19,080 --> 00:40:20,680
But if you keep your mouth shut,

627
00:40:21,200 --> 00:40:23,040
today you're going to watch your friend

628
00:40:23,120 --> 00:40:24,760
die right in front of you!

629
00:40:33,040 --> 00:40:34,000
What's your choice?

630
00:40:37,520 --> 00:40:39,560
Your friend's life is in your hands.

631
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:41,400
Your choice.

632
00:40:51,280 --> 00:40:52,120
Did you find anything?

633
00:40:52,720 --> 00:40:53,640
Nothing.

634
00:40:53,720 --> 00:40:55,640
We almost found something,
but someone showed up first.

635
00:40:56,680 --> 00:40:58,320
We should go.
Someone might come. Let's go.

636
00:40:58,400 --> 00:40:59,280
-Let's go.
-Go.

637
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:04,800
What do you say?

638
00:41:07,080 --> 00:41:09,160
I'm not here to joke around.

639
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:12,400
Are you going to tell me
who you are or not?

640
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:17,560
Enough.

641
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:20,200
No more chances for them.

642
00:41:20,280 --> 00:41:21,440
Just deal with them.

643
00:41:42,720 --> 00:41:44,040
Hello, Sergeant.

644
00:41:49,240 --> 00:41:50,080
Okay.

645
00:41:54,600 --> 00:41:55,840
Thanks a lot.

646
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:03,440
Let them go.

647
00:42:07,200 --> 00:42:09,200
Why? Who was that?

648
00:42:13,080 --> 00:42:14,040
Sergeant Biew.

649
00:42:15,320 --> 00:42:16,920
He said

650
00:42:17,440 --> 00:42:19,760
Weerachai went to the station
making a scene,

651
00:42:20,560 --> 00:42:22,280
claiming Aew didn't commit suicide.

652
00:42:23,840 --> 00:42:27,000
He said one of our men killed her.

653
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:33,600
That means Aew

654
00:42:34,120 --> 00:42:37,360
was actually secretly in a relationship
with Weerachai.

655
00:42:44,280 --> 00:42:46,160
So the police informant is Aew,

656
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:48,360
not these two?

657
00:42:50,320 --> 00:42:51,160
Yes.

658
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:59,960
So we're not suspects anymore, right?

659
00:43:04,840 --> 00:43:06,200
It was just a test.

660
00:43:08,320 --> 00:43:09,920
-We can go back now.
-Let's go.

661
00:43:21,760 --> 00:43:23,360
Reopen the case!

662
00:43:23,440 --> 00:43:25,400
My girlfriend didn't commit suicide!

663
00:43:26,280 --> 00:43:27,360
Police!

664
00:43:27,440 --> 00:43:28,840
Reopen the case!

665
00:43:31,640 --> 00:43:32,840
What are you yelling about?

666
00:43:32,920 --> 00:43:34,520
The case is closed.

667
00:43:34,600 --> 00:43:36,360
There's no point making a scene.

668
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:40,800
Sergeant.

669
00:43:41,400 --> 00:43:42,400
Enough talking.

670
00:43:43,520 --> 00:43:45,160
Check his criminal record.

671
00:43:45,800 --> 00:43:48,000
If there's anything, just arrest him.

672
00:43:55,080 --> 00:43:56,720
At Chaiya's house,

673
00:43:57,240 --> 00:43:59,400
is there really nothing suspicious?

674
00:44:00,760 --> 00:44:02,120
There's a photo of Sergeant Yot there.

675
00:44:03,600 --> 00:44:06,640
Maybe he's working for Sergeant Yot?

676
00:44:09,040 --> 00:44:10,560
Come on, you idiot.

677
00:44:11,320 --> 00:44:13,200
Sergeant Yot has been dead
for a long time.

678
00:44:13,800 --> 00:44:16,480
And he said from the start
he's his nephew.

679
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:18,120
Everyone in Khok Ta Yu knows that.

680
00:44:18,200 --> 00:44:20,080
What's so strange about that?

681
00:44:27,480 --> 00:44:29,040
There are no signs of a search
in the room,

682
00:44:30,280 --> 00:44:33,640
which means they still haven't found
the information we collected.

683
00:44:36,000 --> 00:44:37,320
From now on,

684
00:44:38,040 --> 00:44:40,200
they'll definitely be keeping
an eye on us.

685
00:44:42,280 --> 00:44:43,960
We should've realized from the start

686
00:44:44,480 --> 00:44:46,520
why they suddenly called us over.

687
00:44:48,360 --> 00:44:49,520
It's my fault

688
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:51,360
for not being at the house.

689
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:54,760
No one's at fault here.

690
00:44:55,400 --> 00:44:56,320
Don't blame yourself.

691
00:44:59,000 --> 00:45:00,480
So what do we do next?

692
00:45:01,280 --> 00:45:02,800
Move everything out first.

693
00:45:03,480 --> 00:45:05,520
Burn whatever can be burned.

694
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:09,320
Separate anything

695
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:10,720
that's saved as files.

696
00:45:13,160 --> 00:45:14,560
Where are we going to keep the rest?

697
00:45:36,920 --> 00:45:39,400
There's one thing that seems suspicious.

698
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:41,200
What is it?

699
00:45:42,200 --> 00:45:45,720
In that house, there was one room
I managed to open.

700
00:45:45,800 --> 00:45:48,960
But before I could see what was inside,
I had to run out first.

701
00:45:49,560 --> 00:45:51,320
I think it must be a secret room.

702
00:45:52,800 --> 00:45:54,240
-A secret room?
-Yes.

703
00:45:54,880 --> 00:45:57,640
I think they're definitely hiding

704
00:45:57,720 --> 00:45:59,480
something in there.

705
00:46:01,280 --> 00:46:03,040
If that's the case,
we still can't trust them.

706
00:46:07,160 --> 00:46:08,360
Tomorrow,

707
00:46:08,960 --> 00:46:10,960
send men to watch their house.

708
00:46:11,560 --> 00:46:13,160
If anything looks suspicious,

709
00:46:13,240 --> 00:46:15,040
report to me immediately.

710
00:46:15,120 --> 00:46:16,320
Yes, Boss.

711
00:46:16,960 --> 00:46:17,920
Yes, Boss.

712
00:46:29,480 --> 00:46:30,600
Ma'am.

713
00:46:30,680 --> 00:46:32,120
You look all beat up.

714
00:46:34,160 --> 00:46:35,760
Water. Give me some water.

715
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:46,320
Feeling better now, ma'am?

716
00:46:53,400 --> 00:46:56,240
You'll see Aunt Wilai
this afternoon, Puna.

717
00:46:56,320 --> 00:46:58,320
-She's back already?
-Yeah.

718
00:46:58,840 --> 00:47:01,680
But she went to the clinic in town
to have her wound cleaned.

719
00:47:02,200 --> 00:47:05,720
Then let's hurry home and cook for her.

720
00:47:05,800 --> 00:47:06,640
Sure.

721
00:47:06,720 --> 00:47:07,880
What should we cook, Teacher?

722
00:47:07,960 --> 00:47:10,400
-Stir-fried pork would be perfect.
-Yay!

723
00:47:22,240 --> 00:47:23,160
Yes, Mr. Sonrak.

724
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:25,120
Hello, Puna.

725
00:47:25,720 --> 00:47:26,600
Where are you?

726
00:47:28,080 --> 00:47:30,280
I'm at Teacher Mueangphrai's house today.

727
00:47:30,360 --> 00:47:32,280
Alright then, I'll come over.

728
00:47:49,000 --> 00:47:51,560
Did you hear where Mr. Sonrak is going?

729
00:47:51,640 --> 00:47:52,920
I don't know.

730
00:47:53,440 --> 00:47:56,880
If we want to know,
I think we should follow him.

731
00:48:01,360 --> 00:48:02,920
Mr. Sonrak is coming here, Teacher.

732
00:48:03,000 --> 00:48:05,560
Good thing Wilai went to the hospital.

733
00:48:06,600 --> 00:48:08,760
But I really don't want him
getting involved here.

734
00:48:16,480 --> 00:48:17,440
Alright then.

735
00:48:18,240 --> 00:48:19,960
If he comes, you take care of him a bit.

736
00:48:22,280 --> 00:48:23,320
No more questions.

737
00:48:25,720 --> 00:48:28,960
I'll figure out how to deal with him.

738
00:48:29,880 --> 00:48:30,920
How are you going to deal with him?

739
00:48:39,440 --> 00:48:41,000
This is Uncle Tharin's amulet.

740
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:43,800
He gave it to me to wear when I was a kid.

741
00:48:43,880 --> 00:48:45,520
But I want you to wear it.

742
00:48:46,360 --> 00:48:47,840
So you'll be safe.

743
00:48:47,920 --> 00:48:49,000
Teacher, this song is…

744
00:48:49,080 --> 00:48:50,280
Yes.

745
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:52,320
"Soft Heart" lyrics.

746
00:48:53,000 --> 00:48:56,640
Why did Uncle Tharin
forbid me from singing this song?

747
00:48:56,720 --> 00:48:59,200
I'll tell you the truth.

748
00:48:59,280 --> 00:49:02,000
You knew his reason?

749
00:49:02,080 --> 00:49:04,280
NEXT EPISODE

750
00:52:03,360 --> 00:52:05,840
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
